Maxim Group Overview: Founded in 2002, Maxim Group is a leading full-service investment banking, securities and wealth management firm headquartered in New York. We provide a full array of financial services including investment banking; private wealth management; and global institutional equity, fixed income and derivative sales & trading, equity research and prime brokerage services to a diverse range of corporate clients, institutional investors and high net worth individuals.
Title Investment Banking Senior Associate or Vice President Categories Investment Banking Salary Salary + Bonus Post Date 2018-12-14 Position Type Full Time Job Location New York City Job DescriptionMaxim Group LLC is looking to add a Senior Associate or Vice President within the Investment Banking group, based in New York City.

We are a leading full-service global investment banking firm headquartered in New York City. We provide a full array of financial services including investment banking; private wealth management; and global institutional equity, fixed income and derivative sales & trading, equity research and prime brokerage services to a diverse range of corporate clients, institutional investors and high net worth individuals.

The Investment Banking division provides capital and general advisory services to public and private companies in the small to mid-cap market sector. We specialize in deal origination and completed over 75 transactions per year over the last five including IPOs, M&A, PIPEs, CMPOs, Registered Direct Offerings, and Rights Offerings as lead manager and or co manager. We recently launched our 506c/Reg A + platform M-Vest and continue to innovate and adapt to our client’s needs by engaging a new investor base online. Primary Responsibilities• Transaction execution, new business preparation and meetings, and such other duties;

• Help identify and pursue investment banking business opportunities;

• Support senior bankers on transaction execution and new business origination;

• Assist in the evaluation of corporate clients’ strategic positioning and development of recommendations on potential strategic actions and capital raising;

• Oversee Associates and Analysts involved with transaction execution, development of pitch books and related client materials;

• Conduct and oversee due diligence procedures for active engagements and vetting new business opportunities, including review of and preparation of financial models;

• Assist senior bankers in preparing for commitment committee meetings;

• Review and comply with Firm Policies applicable to business activities;

• Other such duties, responsibilities and authority as may be reasonably required. Qualifications• Bachelor’s degree or MBA, MA, or MS or equivalent with emphasis in finance/accounting;

• Minimum 5 years of Investment Banking experience including public equity transaction experience;

• Quantitative and qualitative analytical skills; strong knowledge of economics; finance and accounting;

• Solid understanding of investment banking products, including equity, debt, convertible securities and mergers and acquisitions;

• Highly motivated, committee and responsible, with an ability to manage conflicting priorities and requests;

• Proficient with Microsoft office (Excel, PowerPoint, Word) and experience with financial programs (CapitalIQ, Bloomberg, Thomson Reuters, etc.);

• Strong leadership and management skills;

• Excellent oral and written communication skills;

• High standards of professionalism and ethical conduct;

• FINRA Licenses: Series 79

Ritter Communications has been at the forefront of the local communications industry for more than a century. We began providing telephone service in Northeast Arkansas in 1906. Since then, Ritter has become a regional telecommunications provider delivering a broad and competitive range of communications products and services to businesses and residents in Northeast and North Central Arkansas and West Tennessee. By providing our Business Services customers with the most innovative and integrated technology and services, were dedicated to reducing their costs and maximizing their profits with customized connectivity solutions. Our Residential Services customers enjoy lightning fast Internet speeds, cable TV and HDTV and reliable local and long distance phone service. Our services are delivered and supported by a dependable team of local industry experts.We are looking for a Financial Analyst to join our team.

General Summary:

The Financial Analyst is key in interpreting business situations in order to develop quality, timely, and impactful financial analysis and effectively communicate the financial implications in a collaborative manner. This role regularly interprets complex financial information and translates into graphs, charts, infographics, and other presentation materials.

Additional duties include: assisting and supporting the financial planning process and procedures, evaluating data, preparing forecasts, and analyzing trends in all departments of the organization, preparing and distributing financial plans, results and reports for internal and external stakeholders, working with a variety of stakeholders, helping them to solve problems and achieve goals and presents complex ideas, models, plans and reports to small and large groups, and presenting to executives and other company leadership.

Essential Job Functions:

• Evaluates and quantifies impacts of various business scenarios and plans: provides detailed analytical support for ROI and other financial components of capital projects, new business opportunities, IT projects, sales and marketing initiatives, etc;

• Analyzes financial performance of the business, recognizing opportunities and concerns as they arise and consulting with other team members to develop alternatives for improving financial performance, and identify emerging financial trends;

• Develops plan models and templates including revenue, cost of sales, operating expenses, capital expenditures, balance sheets, cash flow;

• Develops labor and benefits projections (annual, forecasts and strategic) including capitalized labor projections;

• Assists and supports budget owners with completion of individual plans and forecasts submissions;

• Analyzes plans and forecasts, review for reasonableness, explain key variances create bridges from prior projections/results;

• Administers the planning and reporting software (Adaptive Planning);

• Supports the entire organization as a subject matter expert for Adaptive Planning;

• Identifies and implements process improvements for FP&A and related processes;

• Prepares and publishes monthly/quarterly/annual reports including: capital spending reports, Revenue, COS, RGU reports, departmental OpEx analysis, key operational measurement reports, KPIs and etc;

• Creates, tests, distributes, and tracks financial models, reports and dashboards;

• Drafts and presents plan/forecast presentations and period result communications;

• Monitors and reports monthly actual results as compared to plan, forecast, strategic plan, and previous year. Explains key variances in presentation format;

• Prepares board presentations for various entities on a quarterly basis;

• Performs ad-hoc financial analyses at multiple levels of complexity which may include calculations of rate of return, depreciation, working capital, investments, planning, cost analysis, and financial and expense performance comparisons;

• Travels to customer sites, project areas, business related events, and other Ritter Communications locations as required.

• Other related duties and projects as assigned to support the Finance function.

Knowledge, Skills, and Abilities:

• Knowledge of facts and trends impacting the business, with a thorough understanding of functional relationships and activity;

• Knowledge of Company policies, procedures, products, and services;

• Skill in transforming complex information into PowerPoint presentations;

• High level of proficiency in MS PowerPoint and MS Excel;

• Skill in technical finance with a strong understanding of accounting principles and financial statement relationships;

• Skill with planning, financial analysis and financial modeling - supporting multiple functional areas across the organization (i.e. sales, operations, marketing, HR, IT, etc.);

• Skill in spreadsheet modeling;

• Ability to maintain analytical insight and curiosity with a strong bias toward continuous learning;

• Ability to extrapolate data patterns and complete timely analysis despite ambiguous or incomplete data sets;

• Ability to collect data, research and synthesize complex or diverse information with focus on problem resolution;

• Ability to think critically, ask effective questions, and draw appropriate conclusions;

• Ability to review financial work to ensure data ties out, makes sense, and solves the question(s) asked;

• Ability to maintain quality output quality assurance on ones own work;

• Ability to interface with all levels of the organization with a collaborative, partnering mentality;

• Ability to organize, prioritize and handle multiple assignments simultaneously and to maintain high levels of confidentiality when dealing with company information;

• Strong verbal and written communication skills combined with effective presentation skills;

• Ability to travel for business requirements; must possess a valid Drivers License with a satisfactory driving record.

Education and Experience:

Bachelors degree in Finance or Accounting, plus one to three years of experience in finance, accounting, or analytics or equivalent combination of education and experience preferred. MBA/CPA/CMA a plus.

Experience with Planning and Reporting systems such as Adaptive Planning a plus.

Ritter Communications is an equal opportunity and affirmative action employer; all qualified candidates are encouraged to apply. M/F/D/V.

We strive to maintain a drug-free workplace.

We offer competitive compensation and an outstanding benefits package including health, dental, vision, cancer, accident and life insurance, short-term and long-term disability, 401(k) with company match, flexible spending accounts, free gym membership, company discounts, tuition reimbursement, paid training, paid leave, and much more!

Equal Opportunity Employer/Protected Veterans/Individuals with Disabilities

The contractor will not discharge or in any other manner discriminate against employees or applicants because they have inquired about, discussed, or disclosed their own pay or the pay of another employee or applicant. However, employees who have access to the compensation information of other employees or applicants as a part of their essential job functions cannot disclose the pay of other employees or applicants to individuals who do not otherwise have access to compensation information, unless the disclosure is (a) in response to a formal complaint or charge, (b) in furtherance of an investigation, proceeding, hearing, or action, including an investigation conducted by the employer, or (c) consistent with the contractors legal duty to furnish information. 41 CFR 60-1.35(c)

